				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Enough is enough. Please, for the love of all that is holy, unshackle me. The way IRE works now, I basically spent the AA cost to *lower* my damage output on raids, xp groups, and LDoN adventures. 
<br />

<br />
Please, at the very least: Change the IRE description to be correct and refund all IRE points spent.
<br />

<br />
or: Add a toggle to turn IRE on/off. Feel free to charge AA points for this!
<br />

<br />
or (even better): use the best of either formula when the mage has IRE -- feel free to charge AA points for this!
<br />

<br />
Yes, I know there are some solo advantages to IRE as it is (more mana for partially damaged earth pet) -- but the downside is disgusting, sad, and depressing. Please, please fix this.
<br />

<br />
Thanks.<br />_________________<br />- Sage <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27524">Sehra</A>, Arch Convoker of <A HREF="http://company.mpguild.com">The Company</A>, Bertoxxulous Server.
<br />
Grandmistress Tailor, Fletcher, Baker, Potter, Brewer, and Jeweller. 23 points of Smithing to go!
<br />
Keeper of The Orb, Blessed of Brell, Ally of the Sarnak.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
