			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There is one fix that would allow us to fix the "problems" with Improved Reclaim without changing the nature of the effect:
<br />

<br />
INCREASE THE CASTING COST OF THE P.O.P PETS TO 600 MANA!
<br />

<br />
Chainers (like myself) would be happy.  Non-chainers would get an improved pet canni.  People who don't have Improved Reclaim wouldn't get much mana from PoP pets.  Improved Reclaim would then be exactly as advertised.
<br />

<br />
Those who use a vested pet strategy wouldn't care too much, seeing that the Epic is 500 mana as it is.  600 mana is not a big price to pay for a vested pet (Necros pay 800 mana, a bone chip, and a Peridot for theirs).  Also, it makes little sense that pets that are significantly better than our Greater Vocarate pets wind up costing the same amount of mana.  The Vocarates aren't THAT much better than the Greater Conjuration pets, yet cost 50% more mana.  The Greater Vocarates are not THAT much better than the Vocarates, yet cost 25% additional mana.  The PoP pets are far and away superior to the GV pets, so making them cost 50% more than the GV pets would be right in line, more or less.
<br />

<br />
This is one fix/change I believe most of us can live with.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
