				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">At the same time, I remember that when I was a level 29 mage my pets hit the cost of 200 mana, and they stayed that way all the way through level 50.  One of the wonderfull things of being a mage, was the cheap casting cost of pets versus the large value they offered.
<br />

<br />
Many people chose this class to play for that reason amoung others.  Moving the cost of PoP pets up to 600 would be against that logic.
<br />

<br />
Anyways, only RECLAIM CHAINING would still better, normal chained pets would experience a nerf.  Now you are paying 600 mana for each chained pet instead of 400.  Remember you don't always have the option to reclaim your current pet when you are chaining.
<br />

<br />
As you already observed, normal pet canni would take a large hit too.  We would all need to buy IRE to have canni be usefull.  But there is more then that, Gloves of Dark Summonin, Ancient Symbol of Summoning, and the Diamond Prism of Companionship all lose value because they no longer would help with pet canni.  Since the HP they add does not equate to more net mana per reclaim.
<br />

<br />
I appreciate the creative thought, but I would hate to see the casting cost of our pets be increased 50% just to fix an AA that has been broken since it came out.  I would MUCH RATHER see everybody that had improved reclaim either be given the ability to turn it on and off, or have a chance to have their points refunded.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Eandori Raintree</a></b>
