				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The skill isn't broken.  Pet canni was an unintended side effect to an otherwise useless (IMO) spell.  This much was admitted by the devs.
<br />

<br />
And yes, standard chainers would see a reduction in power, more or less encouraging those who don't have the Improved Reclaim skill to buy it (big whopping 3 points).  What standard chainer in their right mind would prefer not to improve the tactic by investing in Improved Reclaim, especially seeing that if you do, chaining become a more or less manaless event?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Moving the cost of PoP pets up to 600 would be against that logic.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
