		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row2"><span class="name"><a name="102730"></a><b>Booperbustle</b></span><br /><span class="postdetails">The Boopster<br /><br /><br />Joined: 11 Feb 2003<br />Posts: 413<br />Location: USA</span><br /></td>
		<td class="row2" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
			<tr>
				<td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=102730&amp;sid=2bb019f8461178f8bdb3cd488e8ac337#102730"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Fri Nov 14, 2003 11:53 am<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
				<td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=102730&amp;sid=2bb019f8461178f8bdb3cd488e8ac337"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The skill isn't broken. Pet canni was an unintended side effect to an otherwise useless (IMO) spell. This much was admitted by the devs.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I have IRE.  I bought it way back before I <span style="font-weight: bold">knew</span> how it worked.  I had never visited these forums, and experimented for myself to find out the ins and outs of being a mage.  Within 10 minutes of spending points in this AA, I no longer wanted it.  Up until that point I was a very pro-canni AND pro-chaining mage.  I knew how both worked via common knowledge from fellow mages and used both while soloing and grouping.  Upon spending points in this AA one of my favorite techniques was effectively crippled to 20% of it's efficiency (if not more).  That is not my idea of how an AA ability should work, whether or not it somehow mirrors the disadvantage with an advantage.  
<br />

<br />
I'm all for agreeing that the skill works as intended.  However, I'm against any AA that directly <span style="font-weight: bold">decreases</span> the efficiency of a class after that class spends points to get that ability.  It doesn't make sense, and it is very much the case in the case of IRE.  Yes, it has strong points in that it improves up on our "pet chaining" ability, but it is very arguable if that is worth the loss of the pet canni power.  No AA ability should adversely affect the abilities of a class period.  
<br />

<br />
My opinion stands:  either they should refund the points to all mages that spent them AND reword the description of the AA to reflect that it does indeed change the way the spell works (i.e. not simply that it "returns more mana per reclaim", which implies <span style="font-weight: bold">all</span> cases) OR they should somehow change the IRE ability to get rid of any adverse effects for buying the skill.
<br />

<br />
Raising the mana cost of the 61+ pets would be a very cheap bandaid fix and one that more mages would be against than for.  Sure it would be the quick and easy fix but it just simply isn't the most universal and efficient way to remedy the negative repercussions of spending points for such an ability.   
<br />

<br />
Again, Jochan, I agree wholeheartedly that it does <span style="font-style: italic">wonders</span> for pet chaining effiency (I've seen that for myself), but it's a sad argument to say that in any way makes up for the loss in pet canni efficiency or in any way justifies that the skill is simply not broken.<br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062" taret=_blank>Sage Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro
<br />
<a href="http://www.furiouspantaloons.org"><i>Furious Pantaloons</i></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
