				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I cannot agree that nerfing our spells is an acceptable fix for a broken skill.  The way to 'fix' it is to make it a seperate spell and make it an activated ability with no cast/recast time that you put on a hotbutton.  That is indeed the best of both worlds, but it makes more sense imo than nerfing spells for the majority of people in order to fix an ability for people who were misled by the awful in game descriptions or who choose to spend their time online playing in a certain way (IRE chaining or similar)
<br />

<br />
Raising the mana cost of pop pets would be a straight across nerf to me.  I have no interest in any of the tactics related to IRE because I have no interest in spending any of my time online getting xp or farming.  It would increase the amount of mana I burn through summoning pets to pull with and reduce my long term damage output.  What I really *want* is our pets to be good enough that I can't gain dps by giving them up in favor of canniing them.  The level of beastlord and necro crying would of course be unbearable.
<br />

<br />
My reality check is: if pet canni makes magicians so massively overpowered why are necros and wizards blowing us away at the highest levels of the game?  (the short answer is FD and conc pants are also massively overpowered) but the point is while maybe pet canni is 'broken' in principle, if you took it away what exactly would we have left?  (the 'best' pets in the game isn't much of an argument when they only do maybe all of 5dps more than the next best pet on a boss mob if that and/or tank an xp mob for all of two-three more rounds of mellee)<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=630419" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Convoke Archly </a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
