				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Have you not noticed we are the proclaimed masters of summoning? Getting more bang for your buck is called efficiency, and the same thing happens to our nukes</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Aye, we are by far the most efficient pet summoners in the game, and raising the PoP pet casting costs to 600 mana would not interfere with that.  As mana costs get higher, Improved Reclaim gets better and better, making this oft repeated "useless skill" more and more useful.
<br />

<br />
The raising of the mana costs will only make pet canni better, as well as making pet chaining better.
<br />

<br />
If we make IR a toggled skill (which I am also in favor of, btw), it will give virtually no benefit to the people who bought the skill in order to improve pet canni.  Of course, it is a huge boon to the chainers, but they way I have been reading it, the majority of magicians prefer not to chain, and many of the chainers prefer not to reclaim chain.  That being realized, the grand majority of the magicians who bought IR bought it to boost their pet canni numbers.  Increasing the mana cost of the PoP pets would give a decided canni advantage to those who bought the skill as opposed to the folks who decided not to buy the skill.  Also, there would be little need to toggle the skill.
<br />

<br />
You can feel free to disagree, as I have about as much influence over the devs as anyone else (i.e. minimal), and the skill as it stands seems unlikely to be changed just because it reduces our max pet canni numbers.  I am already deliriously happy with the skill, so boosting the mana numbers would only be icing on the cake, and not necessary at all.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
