			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I dont like the idea Jochan suggests, "nerfing" the mana cost of our PoP pets to make IRE work as it should is not good, even if a higher mana cost is logical and would be in line with the power of those pets.
<br />

<br />
But I have another suggestion. The main problem with non-IRE pet canni being so good is that pets gain a lot of hp from pet focus items (DPoC, GoDS,...). Now, how about changing regular reclaim so that it bases the mana reclaimed on the hitpoints of the standard, non-focused pet?
<br />

<br />
This would change the reclaim so that you always get the mana from the standard, 4800hp Rathe's Son for example. Focus items would not affect the mana regained anymore.
<br />

<br />
In numbers (borrowing from the library thread on canni), with Rathe's Son:
<br />
400mana cost
<br />
280mana actual cost
<br />
480mana gain on reclaim
<br />
-> 200mana gain per pet
<br />

<br />
With IRE, using GVoc pets:
<br />
400mana cost
<br />
220mana actual cost
<br />
400mana gain on reclaim
<br />
-> 180mana gain per pet
<br />

<br />
As you see, the advantage in pet canni would still be in favor of the non-IRE mage, however much less than before. I would trade that slight advantage for the power IRE offers me in other situations.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=423546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Izudin</a>, 65 Arch Convoker on Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
