			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td class="spaceRow" colspan="2" height="1"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/spacer.gif" alt="" width="1" height="1" /></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row1"><span class="name"><a name="103085"></a><b>Booperbustle</b></span><br /><span class="postdetails">The Boopster<br /><br /><br />Joined: 11 Feb 2003<br />Posts: 413<br />Location: USA</span><br /></td>
		<td class="row1" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
			<tr>
				<td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=103085&amp;sid=2bb019f8461178f8bdb3cd488e8ac337#103085"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Sat Nov 15, 2003 12:11 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
				<td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=103085&amp;sid=2bb019f8461178f8bdb3cd488e8ac337"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">You can feel free to disagree, as I have about as much influence over the devs as anyone else (i.e. minimal), and the skill as it stands seems unlikely to be changed just because it reduces our max pet canni numbers. I am already deliriously happy with the skill, so boosting the mana numbers would only be icing on the cake, and not necessary at all.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
My argument is--if I had <span style="font-weight: bold">known</span> that IRE hampered the amount of mana I get returned from <span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-style: italic">any</span></span> of my pets, I would not have purchased the AA.  If you go back and read the exact description of the AA, it is not correct in all cases.  It states, "This ability increases the amount of mana you receive when reclaiming your pet".  Taken literally, that means <span style="font-weight: bold">any and all</span> timesI use the spell/effect "reclaim energy" to get mana from any of my pets, I should see an improvement in how much mana I get back.  Your argument is that statement is true in at least one case--when pet chaining.  I'll agree with you there, but in doing that the skill lessens the effectiveness of reclaiming a pet (at full health) that without IRE would give superior mana return.  In other words, there remains cases where the AA makes our class less effective.  No AA in the game should do that.
<br />

<br />
If the AA description was rewritten to be more correct, I would have no problems and probably would've thought more about getting the AA before I spent the points.  Alas, the points are spent and while I'm a great pet chainer I don't get near the mana return back as my non-IRE counterparts (my 1-2% versus up to 8-9% per reclaim using Rathe's Son with other mages).  The simple truth is I pet canni a LOT more than I chain pets.  I find little reason or desire to solo much anymore.  My primary reasoning behind pet chaining was to solo more efficiently.  
<br />

<br />
Now while your idea of raising the mana cost of the pets would make IRE more desireable, it's still a really crappy fix.  It would basically be nerfing the non-IRE mages (btw, they outnumber IRE mages by a very large margin) and cause an uproar from them because they're not getting near as much mana as they used to.  It would also open up an avenue for the developers to effectively nerf pet across the board for all mages.
<br />

<br />
It's a very intuitive fix, but I think there must be a better idea out there that would be more sensitive to the mage community (i.e. throwing an "if/else" clause in the reclaim energy formula that considers both pre-IRE mana return and post-IRE mana return and takes the higher value).<br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062" taret=_blank>Sage Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro
<br />
<a href="http://www.furiouspantaloons.org"><i>Furious Pantaloons</i></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
